prompts.prompt: Create a simple menu in Python with options for a user to choose from. The menu should display a list of options and allow the user to select an option by entering a number. After the user selects an option, the program should display a message indicating which option was chosen.

Create a Python code for a menu with 5 main options. Each main option should have 3 sub-options. The program should display the main menu first. When a user selects a main option, it should then display the corresponding sub-options. The user should be able to select a sub-option to perform an action (for now, just print a message). The program should allow returning to the main menu after executing a sub-option.
